I think I have said it before but I love how Americans have a concept of "The Deep South", like there is a more normal moderate South with cowboy hats and country music and stuff and then you enter the deeper South where things get progressively more zany and you have Cajuns etc.
Eventually it's like a bizarre land of swamps, okra, weird dialects and stuff like in that King of The Hill episode where they go to New Orleans
Deep Bulgaria is the isolated villages in the Rhodopes and the desolate stretches of the Northern coast with abandoned cabins

I have been to Demir baba, my uncle lives not too far from the area, there's a trail in the nearby forest with cloth pieces on the trees that you follow on the road, very nice area, the mausoleum itself has stones and stuff that some people supposedly can feel energy coming from.
